"{\"uid\": \"newsus.cgtn.com-news-2024-07-30-China-s-top-athletes-shine-on-day-three-of-Paris-Olympics-1vElcCzodaM-p.html\", \"text\": \"Our Privacy Statement & Cookie Policy  By continuing to browse our site you agree to our use of cookies, revised Privacy Policy and Terms of Use. You can change your cookie settings through your browser.  CGTN  Copied  China's Lian Junjie and Yang Hao compete in the men's synchronized 10m platform diving final at the Paris 2024 Olympic Games on July 29, 2024. PHOTO: SEBASTIEN BOZON / AFP  Top athletes from China put their abilities on display on the third day of the Paris Olympics, shining on the world stage in a variety of competitions.  China's Lian Junjie and Yang Hao celebrate with their gold medals following the men's synchronized 10m platform diving at the Paris 2024 Olympic Games at the Aquatics Centre in Saint-Denis, north of Paris, on July 29, 2024. SEBASTIEN BOZON / AFP  China\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Lian Junjie and Yang Hao were awarded Olympic gold medals after winning the men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s synchronized 10m platform diving at the Paris Olympics on July 29, 2024.  China\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Xu Jiayu won silver in the Men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s 100 meter backstroke final. Xu previously won two silver medals in the 2016 Olympic games and was the first male swimmer from China to win a medal in the backstroke.  China\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Tang Qianting reacts after taking silver in the final of the women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s 100m breaststroke swimming event during the Paris 2024 Olympic Games on July 29, 2024. PHOTO: JONATHAN NACKSTRAND / AFP  China\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s world champion Tang Qianting won the silver medal in the 100 meters breaststroke as South Africa\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Tatjana Smith received the country\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s first gold of the Paris Olympics.  Second-placed China\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s team, winner Japan\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s team and third-placed USA team celebrate during the podium ceremony for the artistic gymnastics men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s team final during the Paris 2024 Olympic Games at the Bercy Arena in Paris, on July 29, 2024. PHOTO: LOIC VENANCE / AFP  Team China also took the silver medal in the men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s team gymnastics.  Defending champion Cheung Ka-long of Hong Kong, China, won gold and retained his title in men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s foil, beating first-time Olympian Filippo Macchi of Italy 15-14 in a disputed bout.  China\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s volleyball team advanced with a 3-2 victory in the preliminary round, over its first opponent, the U.S., on Monday, July 29.  China\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Wang Chuqin (L) and China\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Sun Yingsha (R) play a return to South Korea\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Lim Jonghoon and South Korea\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Shin Yubin during their mixed table tennis doubles semifinals at the Paris 2024 Olympic Games on July 29, 2024. PHOTO: JUNG YEON-JE / AFP  Wang Chuqin and Sun Yingsha secured a 4-2 victory over Lim Jong-hoon and Shin Yu-bin of South Korea in the table tennis mixed doubles semifinals on Monday. They will advance to play Ri Jong-sik and Kim Kum-yong of DPRK in the finals.  For more, check out our exclusive content onCGTN Nowand subscribe to our weekly newsletter,The China Report.  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466\"}"